  <Subject Subject_ID="300056206">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300186622</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>mechanical strength [300186622], mechanical properties [300056192], attributes and properties by specific type [300226808], Attributes and Properties (hierarchy name) [300123559], Physical Attributes Facet [300264087]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The maximum pulling or ductile stress that a material can be subjected too without breakage. It is usually measured by taking a bar of the material and stretching it to destruction. The ultimate tensile strength is the maximum load divided by the bar's cross-sectional area and is measured in newtons per square meter.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046344/Macmillan Encyclopedia 2001 (2000)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>El tiro máximo o tensión ductil que un material puede estar sometido sin quebrarse. Generalmente es medido tomando un trozo del material y forzándolo a su destrucción. La tensión extrema es la carga máxima dividida por el área transversal en cruz y es medida en neutonios por metro cuadrado.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De maximale trek- of rekbelasting waaraan een materiaal kan worden blootgesteld zonder te breken. De belasting wordt gewoonlijk berekend door een staaf van het materiaal uit te rekken totdat deze breekt. De uiteindelijke treksterkte is de maximale belasting gedeeld door het dwarsdoorsnedegebied van de staaf en wordt gemeten in newtons per vierkante meter.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052374/Polytechnisch woordenboek En-Ne (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>材質能夠承受拉扯或延展而不斷裂的最大力量。通常取材質的部份一條加以延伸以破壞它，測試其一截面積範圍的最大乘載力，以牛頓每平方公尺（newtons per square meter）計算，就是其最終抗張強度。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
